content.problemStatement:
As we have learned checkpoints and key variable now lets try to use both of them together. 

We can use checkpoints for:-
- Checking which code block is giving wrong answer(Code Block means numerous lines of code creating a relevant information).
- Deeply try to debug the given code block by, finding out the key variables and printing those key variable repetitively in each line. \
**Showing a basic structure of how to use key variables with checkpoints** 
```cpp
// assuming that we find out that checkpoint1 was missing out on something
public class Main {

    static void funct1() {
        // line1
        // System.out.println(cnt + "\n"); // tracing key variable

        // line2
        // line3
        // System.out.println(cnt + "\n"); // tracing key variable
        // line4
        // line5
        // System.out.println(cnt + "\n"); // tracing key variable
    }

    static void funct2() {
        // line1
        // line2
        // line3
        // line4
        // line5
    }

    static void funct3() {
        // line1
        // line2
        // line3
        // line4
        // line5
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        funct1();
        // checkpoint1
        funct2();
        // checkpoint2
        funct3();
        // checkpoint3
    }
}


```

